<servinfosub id = "S8T40A1446022003">
<title>
Camshaft Journal Wear
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Check camshaft journals and camshaft housings for pitting, scratches, wear or damage.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If any defective condition is found, replace camshaft or cylinder head with housings. Never replace cylinder head without replacing housings.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH0B140082.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "39.655mm" ver = "01" gw = "89" gh = "95"/>
</figure>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Check clearance using gauging plastic as follows.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean housings and camshaft journals.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove all valve lash adjusters and valve rocker arms.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install camshafts to cylinder head.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Place a piece of gauging plastic to full width of journal of camshaft (parallel to camshaft).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install camshaft housing referring to steps 2) to 4) of &#8220;Installation&#8221; under 
<intxref refid = "S8T40A1446021">Camshaft, CMP Actuator, Valve Lash Adjuster and Valve Rocker Arm Removal and Installation:N32A</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove housing, and using scale (2) on gauging plastic envelop, measure gauging plastic (1) width at its widest point.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Camshaft journal clearance
</title>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
